Your Autobiography

Part 1: The Birth of You:

Were you a planned baby?: yup
Were you the first?: nope, second
Who was present at your birth?: my parents
Were your parents married when you were born?: yep
What is your birthdate?: 12.13.90

Part 2: The Family

How would you describe your family?: a little crazy :D
Are your parents married? yea
Siblings or an only child?: sibs
If you have siblings are you oldest, middle, or youngest?: second
What are your siblings names and ages?: pat becka tim
Which parent do you get along with best?: neither very well, trying to get better
What do you fight about?: time and orginization
Do you have step parents?: no

Part 3: The Friends

Do you have more than one best friend?: umm. i dont know.
Who are your best friends?: i dont know at this point in time. id say inbal and alex and mike (i dont really know alex and mike taht well though)
What do you like to do when you are together?: laugh. talk. have as much fun as we can.
Do you share the same interests?: somewhat.
Which friend can you tell anything to?: i tell a lot to all of them.

Part 4: Your Personality

How high/low is your self esteem?: ummm its okay right now.
Are you an extrovert or an introvert?: introvert, i try to be an e but its just not who i am.
Are you happy?: most of the time.
Do you live life to the fullest?: im content.

Part 5: Appearance

Are you comforable with the way you look?: yes
Do you have any piercings besides your ears?: nope
Describe your hair.: reddish orange.
What make-up do you wear?: i used to, not much anymore, it hides beauty.
How do you dress?: umm usually jeans and a tee.

Part 6: The Past

Were you a strange child?: i was a kid, all kids are strange.
What did you use to love that you no longer do?: umm, i still love it all, in fact, i played barbies two weeks ago with some girls i babysat, and it was fun.
Do you have the same friends?: were not as close but, hannah vertovec, and cece hill, the whole huntington park gang. :D (i miss you guys)
Was there anything in your past that was traumatizing?: im sure there was 

Part 7: The Future

What is your ambition?: not really sure anymore, ive been changing a lot, i think i wanna play music.
Are you scared of growing old?: no, i want to experience all of life, and im excited to do so
Do you want to get married?: of course, i plan to be a young one like my mom too, she was 21 or 22 i think.

Part 8: The Outdoors

Do you prefer indoors or outdoors?: outdoors
What is your favorite season: spring and fall
Do you like walking in the rain?: yeah

Part 9: Food

Are you a vegetarian?: sometimes ill go vegetarian for a week or month, usually it doesnt last longer than that
What is your favorite fruit?: grapes
What food makes you want to gag?: squash
What is your favorite dessert?: chocolate :D
What is your favorite restaurant?: i dont go out to eat ever.
Are you a fussy eater?: not really.

Part 10: Relationships and Love

Are you single or taken?: single
If taken who is the lucky guy/girl?: myself
Do you think love is the best feeling in the world?: it must be
Do you believe in love at first sight?: i think theres a strong connection at first sight, and you know that something will happen between you two.

Part 11: Experiences

What was one of your greatest experiences?: playing music
What was one of your worst?: i cant think of one, i dont like to think of sad things
Have you ever done drugs?: once. :(
Have you ever thought you were going to die?: yeah
Have you ever suffered from depression?: my sisters therapist thinks i do, but i think not

so its been kinda wierd lately. i got a job. im teaching private lessons. have the house alone with my brother for a week. everything seems like its going so good for me. but underneath it all theres like this sadness. but its mixed sort of with happiness. you see, im not the same girl i was last year, even at the beginning of the summer. ive met so many great people. im so different and i think i want things to be this way. the problem is, im having a really hard time letting go. im not really a clingy person but this summer i went through a breakup and i lost my three best friends. we just didnt fit as well. but i cant help to think how sad it makes me when they have sleepovers without me, without even thinking of inviting me. weeks where nobody calls. i feel like part of me has been taken away with them. it just hurts really bad. but i think going through something like this is going to help me grow into the woman i want to be, the woman i will be for the rest of my life. but i just cant let go. its so hard. theyve been my sisters. they know me inside and out. they would do anything for me and me to them. but its all different now. times have changed. but if growing up is gonna hurt this much, im not sure i ever want to. but i have to, i know. and ill make it. i, along with eveyone else, will have to make this journey alone, doing whats best for me and what i love.

So tonight Inbal and I went to see Stas Venglevski. He was really good, and his band. Ive been inspired to learn the accordian, so tomorrow, if Im not on the computer, that is why. yes that is correct, I will be practicing my accordian. I love the nerdyness of that. And at the Stas Venglevski thing we saw Alex and Steve. The happiness of all that is greater than life. Well, yes, today was pretty fun. And Alex showed me the Red Squares stuff, and man, i reallllly realllly like it. It sounds really good. Russian music is awesome. <3 Mar

So this is my first livejournal entry. After deleting my myspace, yes i finally did it, i felt like i still needed to have connections to the internet world. hahaha. so this is my way to "connect." tee hee.
So yes, i was just up north for the weekend and i was able to see my triplet cousins and their brother, who i only see once a year, so it proved to be quite exciting. except, being a red head totally sucks. no joke either. so i put on sunscreen 3 times today, spf 50 too, and i still come out looking like a lobster, and it hurts to wear clothes. yippie for me. but the weekend was fun. i went tubing a lot, and rachel, my cousin, and i finally mastered the "lets switch tubes during the ride thing." and suprising enough, seeing as i have been going up north to my grandparents cottage since i was born, i took my first ever jet ski ride yesterday. and my little cousin drove me, becuase its not legal for me to drive a boat like operating vehicle, a funny thing, yes. and on friday i went to a jazz thing at rotary where i saw mike and his friend alex (i think, im horrible with names) and inbal. woo hoo. it was a pretty fun night, but i wish they would have played some different types of jazz, if you know what i mean, like not all smooth jazz. well thats okay though, cause we had fun and thats all that matters i guess. Well, thats enough to be said for one night i guess.
<3 mar
